body:
### Description

Currently it seem not possible to implement Junit5 Test-Suites like shown here:
https://junit.org/junit5/docs/current/user-guide/#junit-platform-suite-engine-example
I would like to use @Suite-Annotation and Filters...
```
import org.junit.platform.suite.api.IncludeClassNamePatterns;
import org.junit.platform.suite.api.SelectPackages;
import org.junit.platform.suite.api.Suite;

@Suite
@SelectPackages("a.b.c")
@IncludeClassNamePatterns(".*Test")
public class MyTestSuite {

}
```
Quarkus 2.2.1.Final comes with junit-platform-libs (common, engine, launcher) in version 1.7.2.
But it seems that not until version 1.8.1 junit-platform brings @SelectPackages etc.

See zulip-chat https://quarkusio.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/187030-users/topic/Junit5.20Test.20Suites/near/255000165

### Implementation ideas

Update JUnit-Platform libraries to version 1.8.1 (or newer)
